FBIS4-25118 "drchi109__a94010" FBIS-CHI-94-109-A Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 ANNEX Political & Social `Source' Says Beijing May Resume Nuclear Testing in Jun `Source' Says Beijing May Resume Nuclear Testing in Jun OW0106115794 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 1 Jun 94 Morning Edition p 9 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0106115794 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [By correspondent Toshiichiro Amiya] [Text] Beijing, 31 May -- Commenting on information that China is preparing to conduct a nuclear test, an informed source in Beijing said on 31 May, "It is highly possible that China will conduct the nuclear test during June, and its scale would be larger than the nuclear test that China carried out last October." It is believed that with the Clinton administration having renewed most-favored-nation (MFN) trade status for China, which had been an issue pending between the United States and China, the Chinese Government has decided to resume nuclear testing.
